Some have even suggested that people in the commissioner's office have been winking at one another while they make public pronouncements against steroid use. From my perspective, these critics are jumping to unfair conclusions. Before the mid-1990s, the substances of choice in the clubhouse were amphetamines and recreational drugs. An FBI special agent, Greg Stejskal, told the news media last month that he had notified Major League Baseball about 10 years ago that steroid use was a developing problem. At the time, many anabolic steroids were illegal if purchased without a prescription. 